	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think I figured out how to do it.  Have two seperate sets of coordinates, one set will be the playfield coordinates, the other the collision coordinates.  When the player sprite is in walking/standing mode his movement will be calculated with the collision coordinate and converting the updated collision coordinates to playfield coordinates.  When in jumping/falling mode, his movement will be calculated via playfield coordinates, and will be converted to collision coordinates for collision detection.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


